    public interface Datastore
extends Service, DatastoreTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The Datastore interface provides methods for manipulating a datastore.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        Datastore.GetInvocation get(java.lang.String datastore)
        Retrieves information about the datastore indicated by datastore.

        Invocation Result:
        Information about the datastore associated with datastore.

        Parameters:
        datastore - Identifier of the datastore for which information should be retrieved. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: Datastore.
        Returns:
        instance of Datastore.GetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described get operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        NotFound - if the datastore indicated by datastore does not exist.
        ServiceUnavailable - if the system is unable to communicate with a service to complete the request.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user doesn't have the required privileges.

      • list

        Datastore.ListInvocation list()
        Returns information about at most 2500 visible (subject to permission checks) datastores in vCenter matching the DatastoreTypes.FilterSpec.

        Invocation Result:
        Commonly used information about the datastores matching the DatastoreTypes.FilterSpec.

        Returns:
        instance of Datastore.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        InvalidArgument - if the DatastoreTypes.FilterSpec.getTypes() property contains a value that is not supported by the server.
        InvalidArgument - if the DatastoreTypes.FilterSpec.getTypes() property contains a value that is not supported by the server.
        UnableToAllocateResource - if more than 2500 datastores match the DatastoreTypes.FilterSpec.
        ServiceUnavailable - if the system is unable to communicate with a service to complete the request.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if the user doesn't have the required privileges.
